{"kind":"article","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/platformbehavior"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The bundled UI is intentionally opinionated. Each modifier picks the platform-appropriate presentation so consumers don’t have to repeat the conditional compilation themselves, and so the dispatch flow stays symmetric across platforms — the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".paywall(.dismiss)"},{"type":"text","text":" action fires from a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"type":"text","text":" on iOS and from a sheet on macOS."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This article explains the reasoning behind those choices and what is fixed versus configurable."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"revenueCatPaywall","text":"revenueCatPaywall","level":2},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Presentation","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reason"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A subscription paywall is a primary moment, not an interrupt. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"type":"text","text":" keeps the UI immersive, prevents accidental gesture-dismiss, and matches App Store conventions."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"sheet","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"code":"frame(minWidth: 400, minHeight: 600)","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Mac sheets do not expand to fill the parent window. Without an explicit minimum size the paywall would render too small to legibly show plan options. The 400×600 minimum is roughly the size RevenueCatUI’s templates assume.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because neither presentation offers a system dismissal affordance ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"type":"text","text":" has no swipe-to-dismiss; Mac sheets have no default close control), the modifiers show "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":"’s close button by default. Pass "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"displayCloseButton: false"},{"type":"text","text":" only for a hard paywall the user must purchase through — and make sure some other path out of that screen exists."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The minimum frame is hard-coded; it is not exposed as a parameter. If your paywall layout needs more room on macOS, wrap the modified view in a parent that imposes a larger frame, or use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" directly inside a custom "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","text":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","level":2},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Presentation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Reason","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"sheet","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"RevenueCatUI ships a customer center on iOS only. A non-fullscreen ","type":"text"},{"code":"sheet","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is appropriate because customer-center actions are administrative, not part of a purchase flow.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Opens ","type":"text"},{"code":"itms-apps:\/\/apps.apple.com\/account\/subscriptions","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and immediately fires ","type":"text"},{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"RevenueCatUI does not ship a customer center on macOS, and the system has no equivalent in-app surface. The App Store subscription management page is what users expect on the Mac, so the sheet hands off to it and clears its own presentation state immediately.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The macOS branch clears the binding and fires "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss"},{"type":"text","text":" synchronously after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSWorkspace.shared.open"},{"type":"text","text":" so "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState.isCustomerCenterPresented"},{"type":"text","text":" does not get stuck "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". The user returns from App Store to find the app’s UI in its idle state. If nothing on the system handles the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"itms-apps"},{"type":"text","text":" scheme, the hand-off falls back to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"https:\/\/apps.apple.com\/account\/subscriptions"},{"type":"text","text":" web URL in the default browser."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"One-surface-at-a-time","text":"One surface at a time","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The composed "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall(state:offeringIdentifier:displayCloseButton:send:)"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier never asks the platform to present the paywall and the customer center simultaneously — UIKit refuses a second presentation from the same host, which would leave the refused surface’s state flag stuck "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" with nothing on screen. The paywall wins: while "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState.isPresented"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" the customer-center binding reads "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", and a request for either surface while the other is up dispatches "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dismissCustomerCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" so state and screen stay in agreement."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apps wiring the primitive modifiers manually own this rule themselves; keep the two presentation flags mutually exclusive."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Why-no-platform-override-hooks","text":"Why no platform-override hooks","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both modifiers are deliberately parameter-light: an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isPresented: Binding<Bool>"},{"type":"text","text":", an optional "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss: () -> Void"},{"type":"text","text":", and — on the paywall only — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"displayCloseButton:"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"offeringIdentifier:"},{"type":"text","text":". There is no "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"paywallStyle:"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"presentationKind:"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The reasoning: any consumer that needs to deviate from the chosen presentation already has the underlying RevenueCatUI types ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":") and SwiftUI’s full presentation surface ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"popover"},{"type":"text","text":", custom containers). The bundled modifiers exist to handle the 95% case in one line — when the 5% case applies, drop down to RevenueCatUI directly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This package does not try to be the complete paywall-UI library. It is the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"integration layer","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" that makes the common case trivial."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"What-is-configurable","text":"What is configurable","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The configurable surface lives in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI"},{"type":"text","text":" and on the paywall plugin:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Paywall content, copy, and template"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — configured in the RevenueCat dashboard. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" renders whichever offering and template the dashboard returns."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Customer-center labels, sections, and actions"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — configured in the RevenueCat dashboard. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":" renders whichever configuration the dashboard returns."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Close button"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"displayCloseButton:"},{"type":"text","text":" on the paywall modifiers. Defaults to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":"; pass "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" for a hard paywall."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Presentation triggering"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — driven by the plugin via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState.isPresented"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isCustomerCenterPresented"},{"type":"text","text":". Your code chooses "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"when"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to set them via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".request(reason:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".presentCustomerCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" actions."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Dismiss behavior"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — dismiss actions are dispatched by the presentation bindings themselves ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dismiss"},{"type":"text","text":" for the paywall, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dismissCustomerCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" for the customer center). The primitive modifiers’ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss"},{"type":"text","text":" callbacks are purely additive — use them for analytics hooks or cleanup, not for dispatch."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Offering selection"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"offeringIdentifier:"},{"type":"text","text":" on the paywall modifiers presents a specific RevenueCat offering (a win-back or regional offer, for example). Omit it for the dashboard’s current offering. An unknown identifier or a failed fetch falls back to the current offering with a logged warning, so a stale identifier degrades gracefully instead of dead-ending the purchase flow."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Related-Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI"],"title":"Related Documentation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" documentation provides the matching API reference for the modifiers described here."}]},{"anchor":"Explanation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping"],"title":"Explanation","generated":true}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Why the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" modifiers present differently on iOS and macOS, and what is hard-coded."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Platform Behavior"},"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/EntitlementMapping":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","type":"topic","title":"Entitlement Mapping","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/entitlementmapping","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"How RevenueCat’s "},{"code":"CustomerInfo.entitlements","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" translates to Swidux’s "},{"code":"EntitlementSnapshot","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"role":"article","kind":"article"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall","title":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","abstract":[{"text":"RevenueCat adapter for Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallPlugin"},{"type":"text","text":". Implements "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" against "},{"code":"Purchases.shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ships a controllable mock for previews and tests, and pairs with ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for drop-in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":" presentation."}]},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToPresentTheUI":{"type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopresenttheui","abstract":[{"text":"Attach the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"text":" view modifiers from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"text":" to a root view, driven by ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"title":"How to Present the UI"}}}